(298, 1, '2017-12-24 10:11:04', '2017-12-24 10:11:04', 'Let’s start at the beginning: When you add an image to WordPress, whether it be as a Featured Image (previously “post thumbnail”), an image in a post or page, or as a header image, you are actually creating a new Attachment Post. Once the image is added you can edit its Attachment Post by clicking the Media button in WordPress admin. This gives you a list of all the attachment posts associated with uploaded media items on the site.\r\n\r\nDepending on your current theme you may also be able to access the Attachment Post page for the image from the front end of your site, and this attachment page may display some of or all of the meta data associated with the image.', 'ATTACHMENT DETAILS', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'attachment-details__trashed', '', '', '2017-12-24 10:16:19', '2017-12-24 10:16:19', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/wordpress/?p=298', 0, 'post', '', 0),
